origination.corpname: New York State Public Employment Relations Board (PERB)

did.physdesc: Records (documents), collective labor agreements, cd-roms, arbitration files, case files, correspondence.
did.repository: Kheel Center for Labor-Management Documentation and Archives, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Collective bargaining agreements between unions and public employers in New York State.

bioghist.p: The Public Employment Relations Board (PERB) is responsible for assisting in resolving labor-relations disputes between public-employee organizations and agencies of State and local government and school districts. PERB provides mediation, fact-finding, and arbitration services in disputes over contract agreements; it settles questions of union representation; and it hears charges of improper practices by public employers, employees, and employee organizations.
